text: Anna Volodymyrivna Sedokova (born 16 December 1982) is a Ukrainian singer, actress, and television presenter. She is known for being a member of the girl pop group Nu Virgos. She played Diana in the 2011 Russian comedy movie The Pregnant. ==Personal life== Sedokova was born in Kiev, Ukrainian SSR, Soviet Union (now Kyiv, Ukraine) in 1982. She studied at Kyiv National University of Culture and Arts. She continued her studies while also hosting television shows. Sedokova married Belarusian footballer Valyantsin Byalkevich in 2004. The couple divorced in 2006. They had one daughter. Sedokova was married to businessman Maxim Chernyavsky from February 2011 to February 2013. They had one daughter. In May 2017, Sedokova was engaged to businessman Artyom Komarov. They had a son. In August 2017, Sedokova announced that she had ended her relationship with Komarov. In September 2020, she married Latvian professional basketball player Jānis Timma. In late 2024, Sedokova filed for a divorce from Timma. On 16 December, Timma committed suicide on Sedokova's 42nd birthday.
